That's funny.

37:33.567 --> 37:39.819
And all the numbers you see here, they can be found in old book catalogs.

37:39.839 --> 37:41.643
And so what was the catalog scheme?

37:41.683 --> 37:45.590
By a session or did they have any kind of a scheme or subject?

37:45.610 --> 37:49.738
Yes, yes, because Rangel, he had divided his library into it.

37:49.718 --> 37:53.824
different sections depending on what subject it is.

37:53.964 --> 38:05.682
So there are books on theology and on history and on philosophy, but he has also got lots of books in Roman languages, in Italian and Spanish and French, and they are kept together.

38:06.162 --> 38:11.250
It doesn't matter what subject they are written on, but they are kept together.

38:13.734 --> 38:16.257
So if they're ever misplaced, it's going to be impossible to find them.

38:17.419 --> 38:19.422
No, but you have this...

38:19.705 --> 38:24.652
The order of the books has been restored, so for some time it was destroyed.

38:24.933 --> 38:32.784
