39:35.810 --> 39:42.480
No, but I think that Dr. Limberg from Kobe, who was responsible for the library at that time,

39:42.983 --> 39:46.507
he thought it was the only right when to do.

39:46.908 --> 39:48.009
Was he a librarian?

39:48.369 --> 39:49.631
Yes, he was a librarian.

39:49.871 --> 39:51.313
A rare book librarian.

39:51.333 --> 39:51.954
Yes, yes.

39:51.974 --> 39:53.656
The Royal Library, where you were yesterday.

39:54.136 --> 39:54.897
And he's still living.

39:55.298 --> 39:57.280
Yes, and he's still working there.

39:57.340 --> 39:59.643
He was here with Carola, for example.

39:59.663 --> 40:00.904
Carola told you about this.

40:00.944 --> 40:03.948
He was here with us.

40:04.068 --> 40:05.930
How about the original owners?

40:05.970 --> 40:08.333
Did they have anybody who functioned as a librarian?

40:08.482 --> 40:10.084
No, no, they didn't.

40:10.104 --> 40:11.907
I think Carl Gustav Ragnar was quite mean.

40:12.568 --> 40:20.760
So when he had got a quite big collection, somebody was asked to make a catalogue, but it was a very, very simple catalogue.

40:20.800 --> 40:21.601
Inventory?

40:21.681 --> 40:24.445
Yes, yes, more of an inventory.

40:25.186 --> 40:29.012
A short title where the book was printed and what year, but nothing else.

40:29.573 --> 40:36.042
The size was... So really, the books were placed here, and there really was nobody...

40:36.798 --> 40:39.001
No, no, no, not at all.

40:39.962 --> 40:40.603
That's important.

40:40.843 --> 40:41.164
Yes.

40:42.566 --> 40:44.368
It's amazing they survived intact.

40:44.568 --> 40:52.820
Yes, but I think that from time to time, during the last century, people have not been so very interested in this library.

40:52.900 --> 40:58.908
So it has been preserved here, and nobody has been interested in it.

40:59.348 --> 41:02.673
In our time, interest is growing.

41:02.693 --> 41:04.756
Thank you very much.

41:04.776 --> 41:05.877
Yes, yes.

41:06.177 --> 41:07.258
That's amazing.

